## 💻 Development Workflow

### Starting the Server

```bash
# Basic server (auto-reloads on file changes)
bundle exec jekyll serve

# With live reload (instant browser refresh)
bundle exec jekyll serve --livereload

# Include draft posts
bundle exec jekyll serve --drafts

# Custom port
bundle exec jekyll serve --port 4001
```

**Access site:** http://localhost:4000

### File Organization

```
chorigen-help/
├── _config.yml          # Site configuration (title, URL, variables)
├── CNAME                # Custom domain (help.chorigen.com)
├── index.html           # Homepage
├── Gemfile              # Ruby dependencies
│
├── _pages/              # All content pages
│   ├── tutorials/       # Step-by-step guides
│   ├── start/           # Getting started
│   ├── forms/           # Form documentation
│   ├── workflows/       # Workflow docs
│   └── _deprecated/     # Obsolete features
│
├── _layouts/            # Page templates
│   ├── default.html     # Main layout
│   └── fullpage.html    # Full-width layout
│
├── _includes/           # Reusable components
│   └── common/          # Shared partials
│
└── assets/              # Static files
    ├── css/             # Stylesheets
    ├── js/              # JavaScript
    └── img/             # Images
```

### Creating New Pages

**Tutorial pages:**

```markdown
---
layout: default
title: Your Tutorial Title
permalink: /tutorials/your-tutorial
---

# Your Tutorial Title

Tutorial content here...
```

**Adding to navigation:** Edit `_data/navigation.yml` (if exists) or update index pages.

### Auto-Reload Behavior

**Auto-reloads on change:**
- Markdown files (`*.md`)
- HTML files
- Layouts (`_layouts/`)
- Includes (`_includes/`)
- CSS/JS in `assets/`

**Requires server restart:**
- `_config.yml` changes
- `Gemfile` changes (after running `bundle install`)

### Building for Production

```bash
# Build static site (output to _site/)
bundle exec jekyll build

# Build with production environment
JEKYLL_ENV=production bundle exec jekyll build
```

---

## 📁 Project Structure

### Key Files

- **`_config.yml`** — Site configuration, global variables
- **`CNAME`** — Custom domain configuration (help.chorigen.com)
- **`Gemfile`** — Ruby dependencies (Jekyll, plugins)
- **`index.html`** — Homepage

### Content Directories

- **`_pages/tutorials/`** — User tutorials with Tango guides
- **`_pages/start/`** — Getting started guides
- **`_pages/forms/`** — Form reference documentation
- **`_pages/workflows/`** — Workflow documentation
- **`_pages/_deprecated/`** — Deprecated feature docs

### Template Directories

- **`_layouts/`** — Page templates
- **`_includes/`** — Reusable components (header, footer, etc.)

### Assets

- **`assets/css/`** — Stylesheets
- **`assets/js/`** — JavaScript
- **`assets/img/`** — Images

---

## 🚀 Deployment

### GitHub Pages (Production)

**Automatic deployment:**
1. Push changes to `main` branch
2. GitHub Pages builds automatically
3. Site deploys to https://help.chorigen.com

**Configuration:**
- **Repository:** chorigen-io/chorigen-help
- **Branch:** main
- **Folder:** / (root)
- **Custom domain:** help.chorigen.com
- **HTTPS:** Enforced

### DNS Configuration

**Required CNAME record:**
```
Type:  CNAME
Name:  help
Value: chorigen-io.github.io
TTL:   3600 (or Auto)
```

**Verify DNS:**
```bash
nslookup help.chorigen.com
# Should return: chorigen-io.github.io
```

### Deploy Workflow

```bash
# 1. Make changes on feature branch
git checkout -b feature/new-tutorial
# ... make changes ...
git add .
git commit -m "Add new tutorial"
git push -u origin feature/new-tutorial

# 2. Create Pull Request on GitHub
# 3. Review and merge to main
# 4. GitHub Pages deploys automatically (1-2 minutes)
```

