## 🤝 Contributing

### Adding New Tutorials

1. Create file in `_pages/tutorials/your-tutorial.md`
2. Use tutorial template:

```markdown
---
layout: default
title: How to Do Something
permalink: /tutorials/do-something
---

# How to Do Something

**⏱️ Time:** 5 minutes  
**📊 Difficulty:** Beginner  
**✅ Prerequisites:** Account required

## Interactive Tutorial
[Follow this guide →](https://app.tango.us/app/workflow/YOUR-ID)

## Steps
1. Step one
2. Step two
...
```

3. Add to `_pages/tutorials/index.md` catalog
4. Test locally, then submit PR

### Deprecating Features

1. Move page to `_pages/_deprecated/`
2. Add deprecation notice at top:

```markdown
---
layout: default
title: Old Feature (Deprecated)
deprecated: true
replacement: "New Feature"
---

# Old Feature (Deprecated)

⚠️ **This feature was deprecated on [DATE].**

**Use instead:** [New Feature](/path/to/new)  
**Migration guide:** [Migration Guide](/guides/migrate)
```

3. Update `_pages/_deprecated/README.md` index

---

## 🔧 Troubleshooting

### "Command not found: bundle"

**Solution:**
```bash
gem install bundler
```

### "Permission denied" installing gems

**Solution:**
```bash
# Don't use sudo! Configure user-local gem installation:
echo 'export GEM_HOME="$HOME/gems"' >> ~/.bashrc
echo 'export PATH="$HOME/gems/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
```

### "Could not find gem 'jekyll'"

**Solution:**
```bash
bundle install
```

### Server not auto-reloading on Windows

**Solution:** Use native Windows setup (not WSL) or manually restart server after changes.

### Port 4000 already in use

**Solution:**
```bash
# Use different port
bundle exec jekyll serve --port 4001

# Or kill process using port 4000
netstat -ano | findstr :4000
taskkill /PID <PID> /F
```

### Changes to `_config.yml` not reflected

**Solution:** Restart server after editing `_config.yml`.

### Gem installation fails on Windows

**Solution:**
1. Ensure DevKit is installed (use Ruby+Devkit installer)
2. Run in PowerShell (not CMD)
3. Restart terminal after Ruby installation

### "SSL certificate problem" on Windows

**Solution:**
```bash
# Update SSL certificates
gem update --system
```

